The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Thursday, July 01, 2004  Corporate Briefs																								 Ingersoll Rand India Ltd would sell its drilling solutions business in the country to Atlas Copco India Ltd for about Rs 137.52 crore, subject to shareholders nod. The board has approved the sale, the company informed the Bombay Stock Exchange. The drilling solutions business is expected to be transferred to Atlas Copco on completion of all statutory compliances, effective September 1, 2004.																								 Hewlett-Packard India has announced a free bundle offer of its back-up recovery service on purchase of select H-P Compaq notebooks. The scheme provides the customer 500 MB of storage space valid for one year on H-P Datacenter for free, country manager Raghu Raman said.																								 HPL Socomec Pvt Ltd, a switchgear maker, will set up a manufacturing plant in Himachal Pradesh with an investment of Rs 100 crore. The plant would be built on an area of four acre at Jabli in Solan district and would be functional from April next year, sources said.																								 Suraksha, an exclusive showroom of Godrej locks and security products in Calcutta, will offer professional consultancy services regarding selection of locks and provide 24-hour emergency services. The contact numbers for the emergency service department are 9830308850 and 9830146094. ADVERTISEMENT
